# LionMesh TODO

This file tracks the next practical steps required to move LionMesh from prototype toward a credible field-tested MVP.

---

## 1. Project credibility

- [ ] Add `STATUS.md`
- [ ] Add `TEST_RESULTS.md` once real tests have been performed
- [ ] Add screenshots of the WebApp to the README
- [ ] Clearly mark which parts are implemented, experimental, and planned
- [ ] Add a simple two-node setup guide
- [ ] Add a known limitations section

---

## 2. Minimal viable field setup

Goal: prove that LionMesh works with simple, reproducible hardware before extending the SDR layer.

- [ ] Raspberry Pi Node A
- [ ] Raspberry Pi Node B
- [ ] WiFi adapter on both nodes
- [ ] LoRa / Meshtastic device on both nodes
- [ ] GPS source on both nodes
- [ ] Battery or UPS power source
- [ ] WebApp reachable from at least one client device
- [ ] Node A can see Node B
- [ ] Node B can see Node A
- [ ] WebApp displays both nodes
- [ ] Basic mesh communication works
- [ ] System can run without internet

---

## 3. WiFi / batman-adv validation

The WiFi mesh mode should be treated as the first deployable LionMesh mode.

- [ ] Install and configure batman-adv on both nodes
- [ ] Assign static mesh IPs
- [ ] Confirm ping between nodes
- [ ] Measure latency
- [ ] Measure throughput with `iperf3`
- [ ] Test range with omni antennas
- [ ] Test range with improved antennas
- [ ] Document distance, antenna type, TX power and environment
- [ ] Add results to `TEST_RESULTS.md`

Minimum result to document:

```text
Mode: WiFi / batman-adv
Nodes: 2
Distance:
Antenna:
Throughput:
Latency:
Packet loss:
Environment:
Result:
```

---

## 4. LoRa / Meshtastic control plane

The LoRa control plane should be validated separately from the data plane.

- [ ] Confirm Meshtastic device connection
- [ ] Confirm GPS position is available
- [ ] Broadcast Node A position
- [ ] Broadcast Node B position
- [ ] Show both nodes on the WebApp map
- [ ] Test LoRa-only fallback when WiFi/data plane is down
- [ ] Document LoRa RSSI / SNR values
- [ ] Document practical update rate
- [ ] Add results to `TEST_RESULTS.md`

Minimum result to document:

```text
Mode: LoRa / Meshtastic
Nodes: 2
Distance:
RSSI:
SNR:
GPS update interval:
Fallback messaging:
Result:
```

---

## 5. WebApp validation

The WebApp should become the visible proof that LionMesh is useful in the field.

- [ ] Confirm WebApp starts automatically
- [ ] Confirm WebApp is reachable at `http://<node-ip>:8080`
- [ ] Display local node status
- [ ] Display remote nodes
- [ ] Display GPS position
- [ ] Display radio mode
- [ ] Display link quality
- [ ] Display online/offline state
- [ ] Add screenshots to README
- [ ] Add a short WebApp usage section to README

---

## 6. Video over WiFi

Video should first be validated over WiFi before attempting SDR video transport.

- [ ] Start video stream from Node A
- [ ] Receive video stream on Node B or client device
- [ ] Test 720p H.265
- [ ] Test 1080p H.265
- [ ] Measure latency
- [ ] Measure stability
- [ ] Document CPU load on Raspberry Pi
- [ ] Document network load
- [ ] Add results to `TEST_RESULTS.md`

Minimum result to document:

```text
Mode: WiFi video
Resolution:
Codec:
Bitrate:
Latency:
Distance:
CPU load:
Stability:
Result:
```

---

## 7. SDR PHY simulation

The SDR PHY should remain clearly marked as experimental until hardware tests are complete.

- [ ] Run PHY self-test
- [ ] Test all MCS levels in simulation
- [ ] Test all bandwidth settings in simulation
- [ ] Confirm CRC success rate
- [ ] Confirm packet success rate
- [ ] Document simulation results
- [ ] Add simulation results to `TEST_RESULTS.md`

Minimum result to document:

```text
Mode: SDR simulation
Bandwidth:
MCS:
Packet count:
Packet success rate:
CRC failures:
Result:
```

---

## 8. SDR hardware loopback

Before field testing, the LimeSDR / XTRX path should be validated in controlled hardware conditions.

- [ ] Connect LimeSDR Mini 2 or XTRX
- [ ] Confirm SoapySDR detects the device
- [ ] Confirm TX stream starts
- [ ] Confirm RX stream starts
- [ ] Test low-power loopback
- [ ] Test controlled over-the-air short-range link
- [ ] Measure packet success rate
- [ ] Measure stability over time
- [ ] Document frequency, bandwidth, gain and antennas
- [ ] Add results to `TEST_RESULTS.md`

Minimum result to document:

```text
Mode: SDR hardware loopback
Hardware:
Frequency:
Bandwidth:
TX gain:
RX gain:
MCS:
Packet success rate:
Runtime:
Result:
```

---

## 9. SDR field validation

Only after simulation and hardware loopback are stable.

- [ ] Test 2.4 GHz at 5 MHz bandwidth
- [ ] Test 2.4 GHz at 10 MHz bandwidth
- [ ] Test 2.4 GHz at 20 MHz bandwidth
- [ ] Measure range with omni antennas
- [ ] Measure range with directional antennas
- [ ] Document packet loss
- [ ] Document usable throughput
- [ ] Document link recovery behaviour
- [ ] Avoid making operational claims before results are documented

---

## 10. Regulatory documentation

LionMesh should remain clear and responsible regarding radio regulations.

- [ ] Keep 2.4 GHz as recommended general-use band
- [ ] Mark 863 MHz wideband mode as restricted / experimental
- [ ] Avoid presenting 863 MHz 5 MHz OFDM as licence-free general use
- [ ] Document TX power assumptions
- [ ] Document antenna assumptions
- [ ] Document operator responsibility
- [ ] Add Luxembourg / EU regulatory notes if needed

---

## 11. Documentation improvements

- [ ] Add hardware wiring diagram
- [ ] Add simple two-node setup guide
- [ ] Add troubleshooting section
- [ ] Add known limitations section
- [ ] Add screenshots
- [ ] Add architecture diagram as image
- [ ] Add bill of materials
- [ ] Add enclosure photos or renderings

---

## 12. Near-term priority list

Recommended order:

1. Prove WiFi / batman-adv mesh with two Raspberry Pis
2. Prove WebApp node visibility
3. Prove LoRa / Meshtastic GPS discovery
4. Prove video over WiFi
5. Document all results
6. Only then continue SDR hardware work

---

## Current project maturity

```text
Concept: strong
Branding: strong
Architecture: promising
WiFi mesh: first practical target
LoRa control plane: promising
SDR PHY: experimental
Field validation: required
Operational readiness: not yet proven
```
